.SH NAME
nl_langinfo \- language shiznit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
\fB#include <langinfo.h>
.br
.sp
char *nl_langinfo(nl_item\fP \fIitem\fP\fB); \fP
\fB
.br
\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fInl_langinfo\fP() function shall return a pointa ta a string
containin shiznit relevant ta tha particular language
or cultural area defined up in tha programz locale (see \fI<langinfo.h>\fP).
The
manifest constant names n' jointz of \fIitem\fP is defined up in \fI<langinfo.h>\fP.
For example:
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fBnl_langinfo(ABDAY_1)
\fP
.fi
.RE
.LP
would return a pointa ta tha strang \fB"Dom"\fP if tha identified
language was Portuguese, n' \fB"Sun"\fP if the
identified language was Gangsta.
.LP
Calls ta \fIsetlocale\fP() wit a cold-ass lil category correspondin ta tha category
of
\fIitem\fP (see \fI<langinfo.h>\fP), or ta tha category \fILC_ALL
,\fP may
overwrite tha array pointed ta by tha return value.
.LP
Da \fInl_langinfo\fP() function need not be reentrant fo' realz. A function
that aint required ta be reentrant aint required ta be
thread-safe.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.LP
In a locale where \fIlanginfo\fP data aint defined, \fInl_langinfo\fP()
shall return a pointa ta tha correspondin string
in tha POSIX locale. In all locales, \fInl_langinfo\fP() shall return
a pointa ta a empty strang if \fIitem\fP gotz nuff an
invalid setting.
.LP
This pointa may point ta static data dat may be overwritten on the
next call.
.SH ERRORS
